* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/9b460131-3b7d-44af-8655-d812240a81ac/20858.jpg)

*   ## **_TNT Championship: Kyle Fletcher (c) def. Mark Briscoe_**
    

How many times are we going to say this tonight? WHAT A MATCH?!?!?

Mark Briscoe brought EVERYTHING he had and came oh so close, but Kyle Fletcher pulled a turnbuckle brainbuster out of his pocket for the win.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c61f99b3-d921-4ac0-a4cd-fac9bd87f025/20873.jpg)

Toni Storm would simply not give up, or tap out or go to sleep. So she screamed at Kris to "Just fukin k\*ll me!"

Kris Statlander obliged.

*   ## **_Kris Statlander def. Toni Storm to retain the AEW Women's World Championship_**
    

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d1986e17-1b99-4bd7-82f1-77646e9f26c5/processed_20877.jpg)

Mercedes Moné disrespected Kris Statlander who's too tired to retaliate right now. Statlander leaves the ring to Mercedes for her open challenge

Interim ROH Women's TV Champion Mina Shirakawa answers the TBS CHAMPIONSHIP Open Challenge

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3517b06f-e1bd-4c05-87b1-557fad6817aa/processed_20885.jpg)

11\. BELTS. MONE!! HISTORY has been made!!!!!

*   ## **_Mercedes Moné def. Mina Shirakawa to become the Interim Ring of Honor Women's TV Champion!!_**
    

Kris Statlander runs out and takes out Mone during her celebration as payback for what happened before the match!

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2715ac2a-b7df-4ecb-8124-a730e18751fb/20898.jpg)

🚨MATCH OF THE YEAR CANDIDATE!🚨

*   ## **Brody King and Bandido def. Okada and Takeshita in one of the best Tag Team Matches of 2025**
    

At one point, Okada accidentally Rainmakers Takeshita but Okada is NOT broken up about it

"BANDIDO!! NEVER STOP FIGHTING"

Brody King screams at Bandido after a failed attempt at a 21-plex because of an injures arm. Bandido heeds those words and hits a ONE ARMED 21-plex for the win!

